HEADWORD: Mucronated
<hw>Mu"cro*na`ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>mucronatus</ets>, fr.
<ets>mucro</ets> a sharp point: cf. F. <ets>mucron⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Ending abruptly in a sharp point; abruptly tipped with a short and
sharp point; <as>as, a <ex>mucronate</ex> leaf</as>.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Mu"cro*nate*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
